	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Tonga - Eight Sassa officials appeared in the Tonga Magistrate's Court on Friday on charges of committing social grant fraud amounting to R5.5m, Mpumalanga police said. Seven women and a man, aged between 32 and 63, allegedly manipulated the SA Social Security Agency's system by registering able-bodied people as suffering with disabilities for them to receive social grants, Captain Dineo Lucy Sekgotodi said in a statement. They were released on R2 000 bail each. The case was postponed to May 26 for further investigation.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  